Day 3: Images & Lists

Today you'll learn how to display images and create lists, which are used on almost every website.

1. Image Tag (img)

Used to display images.

<img src="profile.jpg" alt="Profile Picture">
Attributes
Attribute	Purpose
src	Image path
alt	Alternative text
width	Image width
height	Image height

Example:

<img src="profile.jpg" alt="My Photo" width="200">
Important

Always use alt.

<img src="profile.jpg" alt="Priyadharshini Profile Picture">

If the image doesn't load, the alt text is shown.

2. Image from Internet
<img src="https://via.placeholder.com/200" alt="Sample Image">
3. Ordered List (ol)

Displays items with numbers.

<ol>
    <li>HTML</li>
    <li>CSS</li>
    <li>JavaScript</li>
</ol>

Output:

1. HTML
2. CSS
3. JavaScript
4. Unordered List (ul)

Displays bullet points.

<ul>
    <li>Java</li>
    <li>Spring Boot</li>
    <li>React</li>
</ul>

Output:

• Java
• Spring Boot
• React
5. List Items (li)

Every list item must be inside <li>.

<ul>
    <li>Apple</li>
    <li>Mango</li>
</ul>
6. Nested Lists

Lists inside lists.

<ul>
    <li>Frontend
        <ul>
            <li>HTML</li>
            <li>CSS</li>
            <li>React</li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>Backend
        <ul>
            <li>Java</li>
            <li>Spring Boot</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

Interview Questions
1. What is the purpose of the alt attribute?

Answer:

The alt attribute provides alternative text for an image if the image cannot be displayed. It also improves accessibility for screen readers.

2. Difference between <ol> and <ul>?

Answer:

<ol> creates an ordered (numbered) list, while <ul> creates an unordered (bulleted) list.

3. What does the src attribute do?

Answer:

The src attribute specifies the path or URL of the image to be displayed.

4. Can we put a list inside another list?

Answer:

Yes, this is called a nested list.

5. Why should we always use alt?

Answer:

It improves accessibility and provides descriptive text if the image fails to load.
